metadata.name: Flying Corset 1
metadata.description:
It is intended to express the recovery of women's self and identity lost due to long-standing restraint and discipline

It is thought that the appearance of a woman choosing her own life and existing as a free spirit can be compared to flying toward the sky.

The abstract line of feeling was set as a tool to the corset representing women's restraint as an object personality, and to a situation of discrimination and oppression.

Through the process of fusing and dismantling corset shapes and lines, and reinterpreting them, women themselves expressed the feeling of flying as the subject of life.
